DAY 43, CIRCUIT BREAKER SERIES
Murgh Saagwala

A tiny twist to the regular recipe. Added a little brocolli to it like the Saag paneer I did a few days ago. Believe me, as strange as it sounds, the brocolli just enhances the taste. @food2goodbypriti Sweetie, the hard core non-vegtarian in me was waiting to try out this version of saag too. Thanks so much once again, it worked super good for chicken too 😘

Will post the recipe in the comments by tonight. 
Vegetarians can just replace the chicken with paneer or tofu 🤷‍♀️
Have a great "last 11 days of CB" peeps!!

Murgh Saagwala Recipe:
Boneless chicken - 250g, cut into bite size pieces
Boiled spinach -1 cup, puree it
Boiled brocolli - 1/2 cup, puree it
Green chilli - 2, chopped
Med size onion - 1, chopped
Tomato- 1, chopped
Ginger-garlic paste - 1tbsp
Kasoori Methi - 1 tbsp (dry fenugreek leaves)
Salt to taste
Turmeric pwd- 1/2 tsp (haldi)
Coriander pwd- 1/2 tsp (dhania pwd)
Garam masala - 1/2 tsp
Fresh cream - 2-3 tbsp
2-3 tbsp desi ghee
Tempering: 2-3 dry red chill, 1tbsp desi ghee, 1/2 tsp chilli pwd. Heat up ghee, add dry chilli, followed by chilli pwd. Turn off heat immediately. Use this as final garnish.
In a pan, put oil, fry onions for a min or two. Add ginger-garlic paste and fry till golden. Add haldi, chilli pwd, dhania pwd, karoori methi. Stir. Add chicken, tomato, green chilli & a little water. Cook covered till chicken 50% cooked. Add spinach, brocolli. Cook till chicken is done. Finally add cream and cook covered for another min or two. Put in a serving bowl. 
Add tempering/ tadka just before serving.
*If you do not want cream, you can add cashewnut paste instead.
